instruction: Find a correlation between two provided datasets.
input:
Dataset A: Age and Gender 
Dataset B: Region and Income
output: There may be a correlation between age and region with regards to income; Regions that tend to have higher incomes have a higher population of individuals in the working-age group (18–64) when compared to lower income regions which tend to have a higher proportion of elderly citizens. Similarly, more affluent regions tend to have a higher proportion of women in the workforce compared to lower income regions.
